"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The `sns.heatmap` function expects a 2D dataset that can be coerced into an ndarray. The 'tips' dataset loaded from seaborn is a DataFrame with multiple columns, but it is not a 2D array suitable for a heatmap directly. The code should specify which numerical data to visualize, typically by using a pivot table or selecting specific columns.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips.pivot_table(index='day', columns='sex', values='total_bill'), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"\n}"